The article discusses the renewed optimism among American manufacturers since the election of President Trump. It highlights the increase in consumer confidence, stock market performance, and improving job numbers as evidence of this optimism. The National Association of Manufacturers believes that Trump's focus on manufacturing and his willingness to listen to manufacturers' concerns has contributed to this positive outlook. The article also mentions various companies, such as Intel and Lockheed-Martin, making investments in the US and creating jobs. Manufacturers are hopeful that Trump will follow through on his promises to reduce regulations, cut taxes, and negotiate favorable trade deals. They are also looking forward to pro-growth tax reform, healthcare, and infrastructure investment plans. The article concludes by stating that manufacturers will continue to work with the administration to create policies that benefit American workers and make manufacturing stronger.